<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870430-0175 </DOCNO><HL> Eastern Utilities HoldersApprove Boost in Shares</HL><DD> 04/30/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> EUA </IN><DATELINE> BOSTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Eastern Utilities Associates said shareholders approved an increase in authorized common shares to 36 million from 16 million. As of March 31, the electric utility had 12,740,000 common shares outstanding.    Eastern Utilities said the additional shares will be available for a stock dividend or stock split should its &quot;board of trustees deem it advisable at a later date.&quot; The shares also will be available for any new business opportunities that may arise, the company added. </TEXT></DOC>